t, I'm not sure you can map a specific DIMM to a specific address within a NUMA region. However, we can at least add the DIMMs to the root-object attributes. In addition, you can certainly map a DIMM to a specific DIMM socket, and I believe that means you can map it to a given NUMA region even if you can't say *where* it is within that region. Have to verify that.<br><br><br><blockquote type="cite"><br>--<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><br>Jeff Squyres<br><a href="mailto:jsquyres@cisco.com">jsquyres@cisco.com</a><br>For corporate legal information go to: http://www.cisco.com/web/about/doing_business/legal/cri/<br><br>_______________________________________________<br>hwloc-devel mailing list<br>hwloc-devel@open-mpi.org<br>Subscription: http://www.open-mpi.org/mailman/listinfo.cgi/hwloc-devel<br>Link to this post: http://www.open-mpi.org/community/lists/hwloc-devel/2014/09/4229.php</blockquote></div></blockquote></div><br></div></body></html>
